&lt;p&gt;Hi Sandrine,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To create a multi-colored effect on your titles, you may need to custom style your headings using CSS, as this functionality is typically not available directly through the editor. You can try the following CSS code inside the &quot;Additional CSS&quot; section in the Customizer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;.your-title-class {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, white 50%, red 50%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make sure to replace `.your-title-class` with the actual class or ID of your title element.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you need assistance with custom CSS, we offer a paid service for this type of customization. You can find more details here https://wolfthemes.com/services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kind regards.&lt;/p&gt;

